# Command tea

## What does this command do:

A command line tool to interact with Gitea servers

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: compile from source into $HOME/go/bin/tea
For Raspberry Pi install using: compile from source into $HOME/go/bin/tea
For Mac install using: `brew install tea`

## Command path

For Fedora run: tea
For Raspberry Pi run: tea
For Mac run: tea

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://gitea.com/gitea/tea/raw/branch/main/README.md

## Command options

# Setup
tea login add                          # add a login (do this first)
tea logout                             # log out
tea whoami                             # show current logged-in user

# Issues
tea issues                             # list open issues for repo in $PWD
tea issue 189                          # view issue 189
tea issues --mine                      # list issues assigned to/created by you

# Pull Requests
tea pulls                              # list open PRs for repo in $PWD
tea pulls --repo $HOME/foo             # list open PRs for repo at path
tea pulls --remote upstream            # list PRs for repo at named remote
tea pulls --repo gitea/tea --login gitea.com  # list PRs for remote repo

# Comments
tea comment 189                        # add a comment to issue/PR 189

# Labels
tea labels                             # list issue labels
tea label create                       # create a label

# Milestones
tea milestones                         # list milestones
tea milestone issues 0.7.0             # view open issues for milestone 0.7.0

# Releases
tea releases                           # list releases
tea release create                     # create a release

# Branches
tea branches                           # list branches

# Repos
tea repos                              # show repository details
tea clone owner/repo                   # clone a repository locally

# Organizations
tea organizations                      # list organizations

# Open in browser
tea open 189                           # open issue/PR 189 in browser
tea open milestones                    # open milestones page in browser

# Notifications
tea notifications --mine               # show your notifications

# Actions (CI secrets & variables)
tea actions secrets list               # list all action secrets
tea actions secrets create API_KEY     # create a secret (prompts for value)
tea actions variables list             # list all action variables
tea actions variables set API_URL https://api.example.com

# Webhooks
tea webhooks list                      # list repository webhooks
tea webhooks list --org myorg          # list organization webhooks
tea webhooks create https://example.com/hook --events push,pull_request

# Shell completions
source <(tea completion bash)          # bash
source <(tea completion zsh)           # zsh
tea completion fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/tea.fish

# Man page
man <(tea man)                         # view man page (bash/zsh)

# Common flags (most subcommands)
# --repo / -r    specify repo by local path or owner/repo slug
# --remote       use repo pointed to by a named git remote
# --login / -l   specify a login instance (e.g. gitea.com)
# --mine         filter to items assigned to/created by you
# -o / --output  output format: simple, table, json
